        <h3><a href="../comment/18179#comment-18179" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Slight correction</a></h3>
    
    <div class="content">
      <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>I think line 474 should read </p>
<p><code> if (currColor[0:3]) != (newColor[1:4]) </code></p>
<p>instead of </p>
<p><code> if (currColor[0:2]) != (newColor[1:3]) </code></p>
<p>The current version doesn't take blue into account when comparing colours, which is a problem if the design has adjacent black and navy squares.</p>
<p>Thanks for this by the way, it's saved me loads of effort :)</p>
</div></div></div>          </div>
